9 COMMITTEE SUBSTITUTE
10 An Act relating to crimes and punishments; defining
terms; creating certain offenses related to gift
11 cards and gift certificates; providing for penalties;
providing for codification; and providing an
12 effective date.
13
14
15
16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
18 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1740.3 of Title 21, unless there
19 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
20 A. For the purposes of this section:
21 1. “Cardholder” means any person to whom a physical or virtual
22 gift card or gift certificate is issued through a purchase or who
23 receives a gift card or gift certificate from another;
24
Req. No. 17446 Page 1

1 2. “Gift card” means card, code, or device that is issued to a
2 consumer on a prepaid basis primarily for personal, family, or
3 household purposes in a specified amount, regardless of whether that
4 amount may be increased or reloaded in exchange for payment and that
5 is redeemable upon presentation at a merchant or multiple merchants.
6 It includes closed-loop gift cards that are redeemable at a single
7 merchant or group of affiliated merchants and open-loop gift cards
8 that are redeemable at multiple unaffiliated merchants for goods or
9 services within the payment card network;
10 3. “Gift certificate” means a written promise that is issued in
11 a specified amount, indicated on its face, and cannot be increased
12 in value, is usable to purchase goods or services only at a single
13 merchant or multiple merchants, and is purchased by a consumer on a
14 prepaid basis in exchange for payment;
15 4. “Issuer” means a person or entity, or agent thereof, who
16 issues gift cards or gift certificates to consumers;
17 5. “Redemption information” means information unique to each
18 gift card or gift certificate; and
19 6. “Value” means the greatest amount of economic loss the owner
20 of the property might reasonably suffer.
21 B. 1. Any person who knowingly and willfully acquires or
22 retains possession of a gift card, gift certificate, or redemption
23 information without the consent of the cardholder or issuer shall,
24
Req. No. 17446 Page 2

1 upon conviction, be guilty of larceny punishable pursuant to Section
2 1702 of Title 21 of the Oklahoma Statutes.
3 2. Any person who knowingly and willfully alters or tampers
4 with a gift card, gift certificate, or the packaging of such items
5 shall, upon conviction, be guilty of forgery in the third degree
6 punishable pursuant to paragraph 3 of Section 1621 of Title 21 of
7 the Oklahoma Statutes.
8 3. Any person who knowingly and willfully devises a scheme to
9 obtain the redemption information to a gift card or gift certificate
10 from a cardholder or issuer by means of false or fraudulent
11 pretenses, representations, or promises shall, upon conviction, be
12 guilty of fraud punishable pursuant to Section 1541.1 of Title 21 of
13 the Oklahoma Statutes.
14 4. Any person who knowingly and willfully uses, for the purpose
15 of obtaining money, goods, services, or anything else of value, a
16 gift card or gift card redemption information that has been obtained
17 in violation of paragraph 1 or 2 of this subsection shall, upon
18 conviction, be guilty of larceny punishable pursuant to Section 1702
19 of Title 21 of the Oklahoma Statutes. If the value of all money,
20 goods, services, and other things of value obtained in violation of
21 this paragraph exceeds Nine Hundred Fifty Dollars ($950.00) in any
22 consecutive six-month period, the person shall, upon conviction, be
23 guilty of grand larceny punishable pursuant to Section 1705 of Title
24 21 of the Oklahoma Statutes.
Req. No. 17446 Page 3

1 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
